1.4  Five-year Accident History



    The MPC Garyville Refinery has had only one release in the past 5 years that requires reporting under the RMP rule requirements.  The consequences of the release affected one worker at the refinery and did not result in any offsite or significant environmental impacts.



1.5  Emergency Response Program Information



The MPC Garyville Refinery maintains a web-based Emergency Response Plan (ERP), which aims to protect employees, public health, and the environment.  The purpose of the ERPlan is to minimize the impact on the refinery and surrounding areas in the event of an emergency situation.  The plan consists of procedures for responding to such emergencies as fires, explosions, hazardous gas or liquid releases, natural disasters, and security threats.  The plan addresses all aspects of emergency response including responsibilities of the Emergency Response Team, coordination of clean-up activities with mutual aid
